            <title>[OPENJPA-2242] Hard coded column size in CAST(? AS VARCHAR(254)) for DB2 caused runtime failure</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-2242</link>
                <project id="12310351" key="OPENJPA">OpenJPA</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When procedure call is used in criteria builder as described in the following code snippet,&lt;br/&gt;
a hard coded column size in CAST(? AS VARCHAR(#)) for DB2 is generated and caused run-time failure with a SQLCODE=-302, SQLSTATE=22001 &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;	CriteriaBuilder cb = em.getCriteriaBuilder();&lt;br/&gt;
	CriteriaQuery&amp;lt;SimpleEntity&amp;gt; criteriaQuery = cb.createQuery(SimpleEntity.class);&lt;br/&gt;
	Root&amp;lt;SimpleEntity&amp;gt; simpleEntity = criteriaQuery.from(SimpleEntity.class);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;	Expression&amp;lt;String&amp;gt; func1 = null;&lt;br/&gt;
	Expression&amp;lt;Double&amp;gt; func2 = null;&lt;br/&gt;
	func2 = cb.function(&lt;br/&gt;
		&quot;st_point&quot;,&lt;br/&gt;
		Double.class,&lt;br/&gt;
		cb.literal(&quot;abcd......&quot;), // error if String.length &amp;gt; 254&lt;br/&gt;
		cb.literal(1003));&lt;br/&gt;
	}&lt;/p&gt;</description>
